56,Diploma in Land Use Planning - Faculty of Management and Development Studies,https://fmds.upou.edu.ph/academics/post-bac/dlup/,0,"Please note that the Professional Regulation Commission (PRC) and the Professional Regulatory Board (PRB) of/for Environmental Planning remain the legal authorities on matters related to the EPLE. Program Goals
The program aims to:
provide a significant increase in access to planning education for personnel of local government units and relevant government line agencies;
provide a strategy for decentralized planning education by offering opportunities for capability-building in planning outside of Metro Manila; and
strengthen the capacity of training institutions at the regional level to support a distance education program in land use planning. Admission Requirements
An undergraduate degree in any field of study is a primary requirement. An admission committee will evaluate applications. Mode of Delivery
DLUP is primarily delivered online. This can be completed within three to four semesters or one and a half to two years. Courses
Course Code
Course Title
Course Description
Number of Units
P201
Fundamentals and Practice of Planning
Theories and concepts in Urban and Regional Planning
3 units
P299
Research Methods in Planning
Major research methods and concepts applicable to planning
3 units
P203
Land Use Planning
Policies, land use planning and control measures for land development
3 units
P214
Planning Analysis
Land Studies and techniques of spatial analysis
3 units
P213
Urban Plan Implementation
Administrative, fiscal, legal and other tools for urban plan implementation
3 units
P222
Resource Use and Development
Effects of resources use and development on social, technical and economic problems
3 units
P210.1
Urban Planning Workshop
Practical exercises in Urban Planning
3 units
Program of Study
Students are expected to take the courses in the following sequence:
Year
First Semester
