The program aims to:
Develop professional valuers and property managers whose standards of practice and service shall be globally competitive and will promote the growth of the real estate industry. Develop professional valuers and property managers who thoroughly understand the land valuation and management sectorâs potential and actual contribution to sustainable development, and are motivated to contribute to bridging this gap. Admission Requirements
To be admitted into DLVM program, an applicant must have a baccalaureate degree in any field. Mode of Instruction
Courses are delivered on a semestral basis (16 weeks) using various technologies where appropriate. The 24-unit Diploma program can be completed in two years of part-time study. Courses
