The Office of the University Registrar
The Office of the University Registrar (OUR) is responsible for student admissions and registration, grade reporting and transcript of records generation, and maintenance of academic records. The OUR aims to guide students throughout their journey in the university from admission to graduation by providing academic resources and references through this website. Learn more about the OUR
Quick Links
UPOU Programs
Learn more about the various degree programs in the undergraduate and graduate levels offered at UP Open University. Academic Procedures
Know the academic procedures (dropping, readmission, LOA, TOC, etc.) at UPOU. The Academic Calendar
Refer to the academic calendar for the important dates in the semester and trimester schedules. Admission Deadlines
Check the important dates for admission in a program at UPOU. Admission to UPOU
Learn about the qualifications and requirements for admission to UP Open University. Enrollment
Find out how to register/enroll and if you are eligible to enroll in courses at UPOU. Course Offering
View the course offerings at UPOU in a particular term. Tuition and Other Fees
Find out how much you will need to study in UPOU. Sample computations are available. Procedures for Payment of Fees
Choose a payment method most convenient for you (bank, credit card, or remittance). Free Tuition for Undergraduates (RA 10931)
Learn the implementing rules and regulations (IRR) of the law in UP context. Scholarships and Student Loan
Avail of scholarship grants and financial assistance."
