Admission to the Graduate Diploma Program
A graduate diploma program is a post-baccalaureate program that can be taken by students with a bachelorâs degree who wish to pursue a masterâs degree in a field other than their BS/BA degree. It provides opportunity to those who prepare for changing careers and profession or as a supportive for those interested in continuing education to familiarize with new modalities in their particular fields *. The UP Open University offers 11 graduate diploma programs, as follows:
(click on the programâs name for more information about the program and its curriculum)
Diploma in Computer Science (DCS)
Diploma in International Health (DIH)
(Ladderized to MIH)
Diploma in Land Use Planning (DLUP)
Diploma in Land Valuation and Management (DLVM)
(Ladderized to MLVM)
Diploma in Language and Literacy Education (DLLE)
(Ladderized to MALLE)
Diploma in Mathematics Teaching (DMT)
Diploma in Research and Development Management (DRDM)
Diploma in Science Teaching (DST)
(Majors: Biology, Chemistry, and Physics)
Diploma in Social Studies Education (DSSE)
(Ladderized to MASSE)
Diploma in Social Work (DSW)
Diploma in Women and Development (DWD)
* Reference:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Postbaccalaureate_program
