Admission to the Professional Teaching Certification Program
The UP Open Universityâs
Professional Teaching Certification (PTC)
program is a non-degree program designed for individuals who have completed a Bachelorâs degree in any field and who intend to teach at the secondary education level. Program Schedule/Offering:
Trimester
Admission Schedule:
1st, 2nd, and 3rd trimester of every academic year
Admission Exam:
Not Applicable
Admission to PTC Guidelines:
(Reference: Clarifications on the Procedures for Admission to PTC document from the Faculty of Education)
For new applicant, admission application may be approved based on the credentials of the applicant and the accomplishment of the admission requirements. Once approved, the student can enroll in the PTC courses offered in each term. Current students of UPOU programs need not apply to PTC if she or he wished to enroll in PTC courses. However, her/his enrollment to the PTC courses should have a prior approval from both program chair of her/his degree program and the program coordinator of PTC. For applicant who is applying for PTC and another UPOU program, both applications can be processed. However, in a case where both applications are approved by the respective program admission committee, the student should choose which program s/he would pursue in the University. If s/he should choose to pursue PTC, s/he should be considered as non-degree student and should not be allowed to apply for a degree program in the University unless, she or he would sever her- or himself from the PTC program. Severing from the PTC program should be done through a clearance. Admission Qualifications and Requirements:
Admission Qualifications
Admission Requirements
Admission Qualifications
Admission Qualifications:
To be admitted to the PTC program, the applicant must:
have satisfied the program-specific requirements specified in the programâs information and curriculum. have submitted the complete documentary requirements for admission before the application deadline; and
have completed the UPOU Distance Education (DE) Readiness Module. Link to the DERM will be emailed by admissions. Admission Requirements
Documentary Admission Requirements:
A. Documents to be mailed to the Office of the University Registrar:
A signed hard copy of the application form generated from the Online Application System. Photocopy of the Official Transcript of Records (OTR) for all degrees earned, both completed and not completed degree programs. One (1) piece 2âł x 2âł ID photo (refer to the photo requirements below). Original copy of birth certificate issued by the Philippine Statistics Authority (PSA)
B. Documents to be uploaded via the Online Application System:
1. Proof of Payment of the Non-refundable Application Fee
PHP 500.00 for Filipino Citizens
USD 100.00 for non-Filipino citizens
Payment instructions are available in the Online Application System. 3."
