Admission to the Bachelors Program
The UP Open University offers two (2) degree programs in the undergraduate level, as follows:
(click on the programâs name for more information about the program and its curriculum)
Bachelor of Arts in Multimedia Studies (BAMS)
Bachelor of Education Studies (BES)
The UPOU Associate in Arts (AA) graduates may proceed to the BAMS or BES program to obtain a Bachelorâs degree. The BAMS and BES programs can also be taken by applicants with previous degree/s. Program Schedule/Offering:
Trimester
Admission Schedule:
BAMS:
every 1st trimester of every academic year
BESÂ  Â  :
1st, 2nd, and 3rd trimester of every academic year
Admission Exam:
UP College Admission Test (UPCAT)
The UPCAT is administered by the Office of Admissions in UP Diliman
The UPCAT is only taken once; qualified transferees are not required to take the UPCAT
The UPCAT is also not required for AA graduates and applicants with previous degree/s. Admission Qualifications and Requirements:
Admission Qualifications
Admission Requirements
Admission Qualifications
The following can apply for admission to BAMS or BES:
Successful UPCAT Applicants;
UPOU AA graduates or graduates of other degree program/s;
Qualified transferees. 1. Admission through the UPCAT (Successful UPCAT Applicant)
Successful UPCAT applicants to UPOU are senior students (i.e. Successful UPCAT applicants should wait an email from the Office of the University Registrar (OUR) for instructions for confirmation of admission. The information about the DERM will also be emailed by admissions. * Instructions for appeals to UPOU will be posted in the announcement. 2. Admission through the completion of the UPOU Associate in Arts (AA) program or other degree program:
To be admitted to the BAMS or BES program, the applicant must:
have completed the Associate in Arts (AA) program of UPOU or a Bachelorâs degree from a recognized tertiary or higher education institution;
have submitted the complete documentary requirements for admission before the application deadline; and
if necessary,Â have completed the UPOU Distance Education (DE) Readiness Module. Link to the DERM will be emailed by admissions."
