Admission Exam:
Undergraduate Assessment Test (UgAT)
The UgAT is designed to assess both scholastic aptitude and the applicantâs capability to undertake independent learning. The UgAT can be taken only once and it consists of the following subtests: Language Proficiency, Reading Comprehension in English and Filipino, Science, and Mathematics. The UgAT is administered by UPOU
Qualified transferees are not required to take the UgAT
